block subSubContent
	p Multiplication can be defined by:
	p
		b Axioms
	p $$\forall a \in \mathbb{N} (a.0=0)$$
	p $$\forall a b \in \mathbb{N} (a.s(b)=a.b+a)$$
	p That is, anything multiplied by \(0\) is \(0\), \(a.(b+1)=a.b+a\).
	p
		b Example
	p Letâ€™s calculate \(2.2\).
	p $$2.2=2.s(1)$$
	p $$2.s(1)=2.1+2$$
	p $$2.1+2=2.s(0)+2$$
	p $$2.s(0)+2=2.0+2+2$$
	p $$2.0+2+2=2+2$$
	p $$2+2=4$$

	p
		b Commutative
	p Multiplication is commutative:
	p $$xy=yx$$
	p
		b Associative
	p Multiplication is associative:
	p $$x(yz)=(xy)z$$
	p
		b Distributive
	p Multiplication is distributive over addition:
	p $$a(b+c)=ab+ac$$
	p $$(a+b)c=ac+bc$$


